          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and knead",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{strong-white-flour}}, {{fine-sea-salt}}, {{caster-sugar}}, and {{instant-yeast}} in a large bowl. Add the warm {{whole-milk}}, {{water}}, and melted {{unsalted-butter}}. Mix to a soft, slightly sticky dough. Knead for 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bulk ferment, 1.5 hours",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape into a ball, place in an oiled bowl, and cover. Leave at room temperature for 1.5 hours until roughly doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and proof, 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Dust a work surface with {{fine-semolina}}. Roll the dough to 2.5 cm thick. Cut rounds with a 9 cm cutter, press straight down, do not twist. Place on a semolina-dusted tray and cover loosely. Leave for 30 minutes until slightly puffed.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook on the griddle, 5 to 6 minutes each side",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat a dry, heavy frying pan or griddle over medium-low heat. Cook the muffins in batches for 5 to 6 minutes per side until pale gold and the sides spring back when pressed. The interior temperature should reach 90°C. Cool on a rack for at least 5 minutes before splitting with a fork.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
